messages.message:
The root cause of the heap buffer overflow is in `xmlDictAddString` (dict.c), specifically this code:

```c
while (pool != NULL) {
    if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)
        goto found_pool;
    ...
}
...
found_pool:
    ret = pool->free;
    memcpy(pool->free, name, namelen);
    pool->free += namelen;
    *(pool->free++) = 0;
```

The check `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` is off by one: it only ensures there is space for `namelen` bytes, but the code writes `namelen` bytes plus a null terminator (`*(pool->free++) = 0;`). This can cause a heap buffer overflow if the pool has exactly `namelen` bytes left.

**Correct fix:**  
Change the check to `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` → `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->free > namelen)` **should become** `if (pool->end - pool->f